            <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_355gc' title='Col. 355GC &mdash; HL Deb 19 May 2004 vol 661 c355GC' name='column_355gc' href='#column_355gc' rel='bookmark'>355GC</a>
            something must be done about it. However, we have a CPA process whereby local authorities are judged and by which fire authorities will be judged and categorised. There is a system within the CPA whereby, if fire authorities are categorised in the same way as local authorities, they will be "fair" or "poor" if they are towards the lower end. With the Audit Commission and the LGA there is a self-help system.</p><p>
